WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.539
Genesis chapter number one this evening,

00:00:02.539 --> 00:00:07.539
and we'll begin our series through the book of Genesis.

00:00:07.880 --> 00:00:10.899
And I'm not sure how long it's going to last,

00:00:10.899 --> 00:00:12.859
but it's going to last a while, amen?

00:00:12.859 --> 00:00:16.739
And there's 50 chapters, and if I did a chapter a week,

00:00:16.739 --> 00:00:19.860
which I guarantee you that's not going to happen,

00:00:19.860 --> 00:00:21.399
it would take almost a year.

00:00:21.399 --> 00:00:23.379
And so it's going to take us some time

00:00:23.379 --> 00:00:24.979
to get through the book of Genesis.

00:00:24.979 --> 00:00:25.819
Thank you, Pierre.

00:00:25.819 --> 00:00:28.020
That's perfect, yeah, I don't want that one on.

00:00:28.020 --> 00:00:29.639
Amen, we're good.

00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:31.340
Amen.

00:00:31.340 --> 00:00:34.799
And so we'll begin here this evening in the bulletin,

00:00:34.799 --> 00:00:36.479
the title for the message in the beginning,

00:00:36.479 --> 00:00:38.139
Genesis one, one, and two.

00:00:38.139 --> 00:00:39.240
I'm not even sure that we're going to get

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:40.520
into verse number two this evening.

00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:41.799
We'll see how that goes.

00:00:41.799 --> 00:00:44.720
But really kind of laying the groundwork, if you will,

00:00:44.720 --> 00:00:47.439
for the study through the book of Genesis.

00:00:47.439 --> 00:00:51.520
I know that several of you have made comment to me,

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:55.759
often in passing, after a service, in some other setting

00:00:55.759 --> 00:00:58.259
as to when we were going to begin this study.

00:00:58.259 --> 00:01:00.779
As I had mentioned it a few times,

00:01:00.779 --> 00:01:04.540
that this was the plan to move into on Sunday evenings,

00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:06.860
and I am thankful for your excitement

00:01:06.860 --> 00:01:09.459
on the desire to study the book of Genesis.

00:01:09.459 --> 00:01:12.260
I believe it is absolutely imperative

00:01:12.260 --> 00:01:16.379
that we have a good understanding of the book of Genesis,

00:01:16.379 --> 00:01:18.239
and we find in our society today

00:01:18.239 --> 00:01:19.779
that much of what is contained,

00:01:19.779 --> 00:01:23.080
especially in the first 11 chapters of the book of Genesis,

00:01:23.080 --> 00:01:26.139
is under great attack in our society.

00:01:26.180 --> 00:01:28.940
As we begin our study through this great book,

00:01:28.940 --> 00:01:30.699
it is important for us to understand

00:01:30.699 --> 00:01:32.779
why we should study the book of Genesis,

00:01:32.779 --> 00:01:34.540
and it's also, I believe, important for us

00:01:34.540 --> 00:01:37.540
to acknowledge the authority of God.

00:01:37.540 --> 00:01:38.900
As we think about the reason

00:01:38.900 --> 00:01:40.500
that we study the book of Genesis,

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:42.459
we would be mindful of the fact

00:01:42.459 --> 00:01:45.099
that many theologians of yesteryear

00:01:45.099 --> 00:01:47.220
have referred to the book of Genesis

00:01:47.220 --> 00:01:51.360
as being the book of beginnings, or the book of origins.

00:01:51.360 --> 00:01:54.860
As we understand that phraseology that would be given

00:01:54.860 --> 00:01:57.860
as to summarizing the book that is before us

00:01:57.860 --> 00:01:59.080
that we'll be studying,

00:01:59.080 --> 00:02:01.540
I believe this evening that a proper understanding

00:02:01.540 --> 00:02:05.459
of the book of Genesis would then enable the believer,

00:02:05.459 --> 00:02:08.460
the child of God, to properly interpret

00:02:08.460 --> 00:02:10.179
the rest of Scripture.

00:02:10.179 --> 00:02:12.740
If you do not have an understanding,

00:02:12.740 --> 00:02:16.279
a proper understanding of this foundational truth

00:02:16.279 --> 00:02:18.220
that is given to us in the book of Genesis,

00:02:18.220 --> 00:02:21.020
it becomes very complicated and very difficult

00:02:21.020 --> 00:02:23.660
for us to understand the rest of Scripture.

00:02:23.740 --> 00:02:27.139
And so we find that this book, the book of Genesis,

00:02:27.139 --> 00:02:29.380
is foundational in nature,

00:02:29.380 --> 00:02:32.259
and it is foundational for the rest of Scripture.

00:02:32.259 --> 00:02:37.179
And I cannot overemphasize that truth this evening.

00:02:37.179 --> 00:02:42.020
And here's the reality, is that because of the truth

00:02:42.020 --> 00:02:45.300
of the importance of the book of Genesis,

00:02:45.300 --> 00:02:48.699
we find that the content of this book

00:02:48.699 --> 00:02:53.339
is under intense, constant attack.

00:02:54.020 --> 00:02:56.740
The book of Genesis is constantly being attacked

00:02:56.740 --> 00:02:59.380
in the classrooms of America,

00:02:59.380 --> 00:03:01.619
in the lives of our young people.

00:03:01.619 --> 00:03:05.139
We find in the universities across the land,

00:03:05.139 --> 00:03:08.380
the truth that is given in the book of Genesis

00:03:08.380 --> 00:03:12.740
is under constant, intense attack.

00:03:12.740 --> 00:03:16.899
And we find that no doubt the one behind that

00:03:16.899 --> 00:03:19.100
is Satan, the enemy of God.

00:03:19.100 --> 00:03:21.339
And we find that even as it's recorded

00:03:21.339 --> 00:03:23.139
in Genesis chapter number three,

00:03:23.940 --> 00:03:26.020
that he says to Eve, yea, hath God said.

00:03:26.020 --> 00:03:29.059
And we've often referenced that passage of Scripture

00:03:29.059 --> 00:03:30.899
in dealing with the fact that Satan

00:03:30.899 --> 00:03:34.220
would constantly attack the word of God.

00:03:34.220 --> 00:03:36.979
But if you understand the foundation of the book of Genesis

00:03:36.979 --> 00:03:39.380
and you see even in this first chapter,

00:03:39.380 --> 00:03:41.220
Genesis chapter number one,

00:03:41.220 --> 00:03:43.100
we find that in this text of Scripture,

00:03:43.100 --> 00:03:46.419
there are 31 verses in Genesis chapter number one,

00:03:46.419 --> 00:03:48.660
and on at least 30 occasions,

00:03:48.660 --> 00:03:52.339
the name God or the reference to God is given.

00:03:52.339 --> 00:03:55.580
Can you understand why Satan would wanna attack

00:03:55.580 --> 00:03:58.660
the truth that is found in Genesis chapter number one

00:03:58.660 --> 00:04:01.339
and really through chapter number 11?

00:04:01.339 --> 00:04:05.419
And we find that this attack is really being intensified.

00:04:05.419 --> 00:04:09.619
We find that it is those that would oppose the truth,

00:04:09.619 --> 00:04:13.380
the teaching of creation and the origin of man

00:04:13.380 --> 00:04:16.739
and all that is contained, the record of the flood

00:04:16.739 --> 00:04:19.260
as it's given beginning in Genesis chapter number six,

00:04:19.260 --> 00:04:23.380
we find that the attack is intensifying

00:04:23.380 --> 00:04:25.899
in these the last days.

00:04:25.899 --> 00:04:27.899
And so therefore, it is imperative

00:04:27.899 --> 00:04:30.100
that we as the people of God,

00:04:30.100 --> 00:04:32.500
that we study the word of God

00:04:32.500 --> 00:04:34.859
because it is absolutely essential

00:04:34.859 --> 00:04:38.700
that we have the foundation for our Christian faith.

00:04:38.700 --> 00:04:39.980
Now, the reality this evening

00:04:39.980 --> 00:04:42.399
is that we have been instructed in the New Testament

00:04:42.399 --> 00:04:44.140
that we're to be students of the word of God,

00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:46.420
study to show thyself approved unto God,

00:04:46.420 --> 00:04:48.339
a workman that needeth not to be ashamed,

00:04:48.339 --> 00:04:51.260
rightly dividing the word of truth.

00:04:51.260 --> 00:04:54.279
And so we find that we have been given the responsibility

00:04:54.279 --> 00:04:57.260
to study, to be students of the word of God.

00:04:57.260 --> 00:04:59.959
Jesus said to those as he was ministering

00:04:59.959 --> 00:05:01.980
and walking upon the earth, those that would oppose him,

00:05:01.980 --> 00:05:04.200
he said, search the scriptures.

00:05:04.200 --> 00:05:06.820
We find that it was on the road to Emmaus

00:05:06.820 --> 00:05:09.359
when he was speaking there after the resurrection

00:05:09.359 --> 00:05:13.459
to those disciples that it says that he began in Moses

00:05:13.459 --> 00:05:15.980
and all the prophets and expounded unto them

00:05:15.980 --> 00:05:18.779
all the things concerning himself

00:05:18.779 --> 00:05:22.000
and how foundational the book of Genesis is.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:23.380
So we understand the importance

00:05:23.380 --> 00:05:25.100
of studying the book of Genesis.

00:05:25.100 --> 00:05:28.500
We need to be able to stand up and give an answer.

00:05:29.899 --> 00:05:31.040
We find that I mentioned,

00:05:31.040 --> 00:05:32.559
not only do we need to understand

00:05:32.559 --> 00:05:33.820
why we should study the book,

00:05:33.820 --> 00:05:37.619
but we need to acknowledge the authority of God.

00:05:37.619 --> 00:05:42.619
I'm thankful this evening that God is the authority, period.

00:05:42.940 --> 00:05:45.260
So often in our society today,

00:05:45.260 --> 00:05:50.220
there's a debate over who is authoritative, who is right,

00:05:50.220 --> 00:05:51.100
who are we gonna believe,

00:05:51.100 --> 00:05:53.739
what voice are we going to listen to?

00:05:53.739 --> 00:05:56.779
And the reality is that we must come to the conclusion

00:05:56.779 --> 00:05:59.019
this evening and acknowledge the fact

00:05:59.019 --> 00:06:04.019
that God is the authority and that he has given us his word

00:06:04.619 --> 00:06:06.660
and his word is authoritative.

00:06:06.660 --> 00:06:09.220
The Bible says in 2 Timothy 3 and verse number 16,

00:06:09.220 --> 00:06:12.579
all scripture, does that include the book of Genesis?

00:06:12.579 --> 00:06:13.739
Absolutely.

00:06:13.739 --> 00:06:18.739
All scripture is given by inspiration of God

00:06:19.059 --> 00:06:20.980
and is profitable.

00:06:20.980 --> 00:06:22.540
And we go through the rest of that verse

00:06:22.540 --> 00:06:24.820
and we understand for doctrine, for reproof, for correction,

00:06:24.820 --> 00:06:26.420
for instruction in righteousness,

00:06:26.420 --> 00:06:28.179
that the man of God might be perfect,

00:06:28.179 --> 00:06:30.339
throughly furnished unto all good works.

00:06:30.339 --> 00:06:35.179
And we find that the word of God, Genesis is God breathed.

00:06:35.179 --> 00:06:36.720
It is God's word.

00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:38.779
Often we look at the human penman and we say, okay,

00:06:38.779 --> 00:06:41.940
so Moses is ascribed as being the human penman

00:06:41.940 --> 00:06:42.940
to the book of Genesis.

00:06:42.940 --> 00:06:44.320
And there are some that would come and say,

00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:47.540
well, Moses was born many years later

00:06:47.540 --> 00:06:50.940
and there's no way that he could give an accurate account

00:06:50.940 --> 00:06:53.579
of that which is recorded in the book of Genesis,

00:06:53.579 --> 00:06:56.640
especially in the first 11 chapters.

00:06:56.640 --> 00:06:58.339
It's God's word.

00:06:58.339 --> 00:06:59.179
Amen?

00:06:59.179 --> 00:07:03.500
It is God's word and we must stand upon that.

00:07:03.500 --> 00:07:06.859
The reality is that this evening there are some

00:07:06.859 --> 00:07:11.100
that would give credence and they would give their attention

00:07:11.100 --> 00:07:14.380
to some other authority and they would believe

00:07:14.380 --> 00:07:18.220
some other authoritative quote-unquote voice,

00:07:18.220 --> 00:07:22.380
somebody that would stand and would seek to proclaim

00:07:22.380 --> 00:07:25.140
and speak with authority some other truth.

00:07:25.140 --> 00:07:27.220
And there are some that would be deceived from that

00:07:27.220 --> 00:07:29.820
or some other teaching, some other theory,

00:07:29.820 --> 00:07:31.500
and they would be deceived by that.

00:07:31.500 --> 00:07:35.339
And so we must establish at the very onset of our study

00:07:35.339 --> 00:07:38.380
that it is God who is the authority

00:07:38.540 --> 00:07:41.260
and it is his word that is authoritative.

00:07:41.260 --> 00:07:44.579
Reality this evening tells us that if I cannot trust God

00:07:44.579 --> 00:07:46.619
with regard to creation,

00:07:46.619 --> 00:07:49.260
how could I trust him with regard to salvation?

00:07:51.859 --> 00:07:56.420
If I can't trust what God says as to the origin of the earth

00:07:56.420 --> 00:08:01.019
how can I trust what he says with relation to that of heaven?

00:08:01.019 --> 00:08:02.579
Does it make sense?

00:08:02.579 --> 00:08:03.859
And this is the problem.

00:08:03.859 --> 00:08:05.579
This is the road by which we go down

00:08:05.579 --> 00:08:08.779
and you find that as we studied even in 1 Corinthians 15

00:08:08.779 --> 00:08:12.420
with the false teaching that was present there in Corinth

00:08:12.420 --> 00:08:14.779
regarding those that said there were some among them

00:08:14.779 --> 00:08:17.140
that said there's no resurrection of the dead

00:08:17.140 --> 00:08:19.700
and Paul said, listen, if that's true

00:08:19.700 --> 00:08:22.700
then here's everything else that's affected by that.

00:08:22.700 --> 00:08:27.019
And what happens is if we throw out the creation account

00:08:27.019 --> 00:08:32.020
it has deep, far-reaching consequences

00:08:32.140 --> 00:08:35.419
because if we can get rid of the book, the creation,

00:08:36.260 --> 00:08:38.020
if we can get rid of the fall and sin entering in the world

00:08:38.020 --> 00:08:40.179
and all of those things, if it's undermined

00:08:40.179 --> 00:08:42.659
there's no sin, there's no fall, there's no death,

00:08:42.659 --> 00:08:44.419
there's no need for a savior.

00:08:44.419 --> 00:08:46.299
And that's exactly the approach

00:08:46.299 --> 00:08:48.059
that the enemy is seeking to take.

00:08:48.059 --> 00:08:50.859
He's saying, listen, the enemy is undermining

00:08:50.859 --> 00:08:52.340
the authority of the word of God,

00:08:52.340 --> 00:08:54.739
specifically the account of creation,

00:08:54.739 --> 00:08:57.580
the creation of the world, the creation of man,

00:08:57.580 --> 00:08:59.900
the fall of man, the flood, so on and so forth.

00:08:59.900 --> 00:09:01.820
And he's undermining all of that

00:09:01.820 --> 00:09:04.099
and he's saying that can't be trusted

00:09:04.099 --> 00:09:06.419
so why do you even need a savior?

00:09:07.539 --> 00:09:09.659
If man evolved from nothing

00:09:09.659 --> 00:09:12.940
and if evolution is what is being taught

00:09:12.940 --> 00:09:14.140
and we know that it is,

00:09:14.140 --> 00:09:17.020
evolution is so prevalent in our society today

00:09:17.020 --> 00:09:18.820
and if evolution is being taught

00:09:18.820 --> 00:09:22.260
and being propagated amongst our young people,

00:09:22.260 --> 00:09:25.739
amongst those within our school systems, our universities,

00:09:25.739 --> 00:09:30.539
we find that the natural conclusion of evolution

00:09:30.539 --> 00:09:34.780
is that we have arrived through this process of evolution

00:09:34.780 --> 00:09:37.059
and therefore we are at this state

00:09:37.059 --> 00:09:39.219
and we have no need for a savior.

00:09:40.219 --> 00:09:43.140
But that is contrary to what God's word teaches

00:09:43.140 --> 00:09:45.140
and I'm thankful that God created,

00:09:45.140 --> 00:09:48.380
he is the creator, he is the sustainer of life

00:09:48.380 --> 00:09:49.580
but I'm thankful this evening

00:09:49.580 --> 00:09:53.739
that not only is he the creator but he is the redeemer

00:09:53.739 --> 00:09:55.979
and it's a precious truth.

00:09:55.979 --> 00:09:58.820
Listen, this evening as we look at the book of Genesis

00:09:58.820 --> 00:09:59.979
and over the next several weeks

00:09:59.979 --> 00:10:03.259
as we begin really studying the creation account

00:10:03.259 --> 00:10:05.579
and looking at all that God says to us

00:10:05.579 --> 00:10:08.659
and all that he reveals to us in this wonderful book

00:10:08.659 --> 00:10:11.419
that we, the book of Genesis that we'll be studying

00:10:11.419 --> 00:10:13.019
that's before us this evening,

00:10:13.019 --> 00:10:16.459
we understand that as we grasp the knowledge

00:10:16.459 --> 00:10:18.179
that is given to us in this book

00:10:18.179 --> 00:10:21.019
and we understand how God would reveal to us

00:10:21.019 --> 00:10:23.619
what he did in those days of creation,

00:10:23.619 --> 00:10:25.979
how it would increase and encourage us,

00:10:25.979 --> 00:10:27.279
it would increase our faith,

00:10:27.279 --> 00:10:30.399
it would encourage us to continue to walk with God.

00:10:31.399 --> 00:10:33.939
And this evening, as we look at this passage of scripture,

00:10:33.939 --> 00:10:37.979
Genesis 1.1, it's only 10 words in our English Bible.

00:10:39.159 --> 00:10:40.299
10 words.

00:10:41.439 --> 00:10:45.119
But if you consider the 10 words of Genesis 1.1

00:10:45.119 --> 00:10:49.599
and you think of the depth and power of these words,

00:10:49.599 --> 00:10:53.959
it is almost beyond our human comprehension.

00:10:53.959 --> 00:10:58.239
The Bible begins in Genesis 1.1,

00:10:58.239 --> 00:11:03.239
in the beginning, God created the heaven and the earth.

00:11:05.239 --> 00:11:06.679
I mean, it's amazing.

00:11:06.679 --> 00:11:09.519
That's how the Bible begins.

00:11:09.519 --> 00:11:12.399
You understand this evening that this verse of scripture,

00:11:12.399 --> 00:11:14.699
it provides us with a summary statement

00:11:14.699 --> 00:11:16.359
of God's creative work.

00:11:16.359 --> 00:11:20.319
In the beginning, God created the heaven and the earth.

00:11:20.319 --> 00:11:21.839
Beginning in verse number two

00:11:21.839 --> 00:11:23.759
and following through the end of the chapter

00:11:24.559 --> 00:11:26.279
and into chapter number two, more details are given,

00:11:26.279 --> 00:11:28.459
but we find that the work of creation

00:11:28.459 --> 00:11:30.399
is explained in greater detail.

00:11:30.399 --> 00:11:32.639
How it is that God created

00:11:32.639 --> 00:11:34.559
and the order by which he created

00:11:34.559 --> 00:11:37.599
and what he created on which day and so on and so forth.

00:11:37.599 --> 00:11:39.819
And we find that, but the Bible begins

00:11:39.819 --> 00:11:42.319
with these 10 powerful words,

00:11:42.319 --> 00:11:47.319
in the beginning, God created the heaven and the earth.

00:11:47.839 --> 00:11:49.839
Now it's important for us to note this evening

00:11:49.839 --> 00:11:52.919
that the Genesis account does not attempt

00:11:52.919 --> 00:11:55.079
to prove the existence of God.

00:11:56.199 --> 00:11:59.159
It doesn't attempt to prove the existence of God.

00:11:59.159 --> 00:12:01.879
It begins with God.

00:12:01.879 --> 00:12:04.079
And we find that no doubt,

00:12:04.079 --> 00:12:07.219
even as we would understand the account of creation

00:12:07.219 --> 00:12:10.139
and we'd read about those patriarchs

00:12:10.139 --> 00:12:12.759
and even getting into the nation of Israel

00:12:12.759 --> 00:12:14.559
and Moses and others,

00:12:14.559 --> 00:12:18.079
they did not doubt the existence of God.

00:12:18.079 --> 00:12:21.559
They were well aware of the fact that God existed.

00:12:21.599 --> 00:12:23.959
In fact, even as you would think about Abraham

00:12:23.959 --> 00:12:26.359
and how he was called out of the Ur of the Chaldees

00:12:26.359 --> 00:12:30.799
and they served a plurality of gods there in that region,

00:12:30.799 --> 00:12:32.719
but Abraham was called out of that

00:12:32.719 --> 00:12:36.199
to understand who the one true God is.

00:12:36.199 --> 00:12:38.759
And here in Genesis one in verse number one,

00:12:38.759 --> 00:12:41.879
we find that God does not seek to prove his existence.

00:12:41.879 --> 00:12:46.719
He simply begins by declaring his existence.

00:12:46.719 --> 00:12:50.999
I'm thankful that God has no beginning and no end.

00:12:50.999 --> 00:12:53.159
As we think about this verse of Scripture

00:12:53.159 --> 00:12:56.079
and we find that the Bible says in the beginning

00:12:56.079 --> 00:12:59.479
that this phrase is obviously there

00:12:59.479 --> 00:13:02.279
from the perspective of God's creation

00:13:02.279 --> 00:13:04.719
because God has always been.

00:13:05.679 --> 00:13:08.639
It's not saying that at God's beginning,

00:13:08.639 --> 00:13:11.159
see God is outside of time.

00:13:11.159 --> 00:13:12.559
Aren't you thankful for that?

00:13:12.559 --> 00:13:14.439
He has no beginning and no ending.

00:13:14.439 --> 00:13:16.119
We'll look at a couple of verses of Scripture here

